This paper deals with a supervised-learning problem and proposes a loss function for training neural networks. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also focuses on image classification tasks, which suggests that it could be classified under Computer Vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of portfolio theory, which is a mathematical framework for managing risk and return, indicating that it could be classified under Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) or Statistics (cs.ST).
